==English==
===Etymology===
Eponym for [[w:Hans Asperger]] + [[syndrome]]
===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-uk-Asperger's syndrome.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Asperger’s [[syndrome]]'''  (abbreviated as ''[[AS]]'')
# a high-function form  of [[Autism]].

The condition is characterised by severe and sustained impairment in [[social]] [[interaction]] and [[communication]].  It is also characterised by restricted, repetitive, stereotyped activities, interests and routines.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[Aspergerin syndrooma]], [[Aspergerin oireyhtymä]]
*German: [[Asperger-Syndrom]] ''n''

